Functions

calc_rich <- function(data, col_start, col_end) {
  columns <- c(col_start:col_end)
  subset_data <- data[, columns]
  positive_columns_per_row <- rowSums(subset_data > 0)
  return(positive_columns_per_row)
}

calc_abun <- function(data, col_start, col_end) {
  columns <- c(col_start:col_end)
  subset_data <- data[, columns]
  total <- rowSums(subset_data)
  return(total)
}

simpsons_diversity <- function(data, col_start, col_end) {
  counts <- as.numeric(row[col_start:col_end])
  counts <- counts[!is.na(counts)]
  n <- sum(counts)
  if (n == 0) return(0)
  proportions <- counts / n
  return(1 - sum(proportions^2))
}

shan_diversity <- function(df, species_cols) {
  # Subset the dataframe to select only the columns with species counts
  species_data <- df[, species_cols]
  
  # Apply the Shannon's diversity formula to each row of the species data
  shannon_index <- apply(species_data, 1, function(counts) {
    total_count <- sum(counts)
    proportions <- counts / total_count
    
    # Shannon's diversity index calculation
    proportions <- proportions[proportions > 0] # remove zeros to avoid log(0)
    -sum(proportions * log(proportions))
  })
  
  return(shannon_index)
}

lagged_clim_data <- clim_data %>%
  select(Lagged_Date, ppt..mm., tmin..degrees.C., tmean..degrees.C., tmax..degrees.C., vpdmin..hPa., vpdmax..hPa.) %>%
  rename(
    lag.ppt = ppt..mm.,
    lag.tmin..degrees.C. = tmin..degrees.C.,
    lag.tmean = tmean..degrees.C.,
    lag.tmax..degrees.C. = tmax..degrees.C.,
    lag.vmin = vpdmin..hPa.,
    lag.vmax = vpdmax..hPa.
  )

# Merge original data with the climate data

  left_join(lagged_clim_data, by = c("Date"= "Lagged_Date"))

Do a repeated measure ANOVA to see the effects of date

options(scipen = 999)
data$Year <- year(data$Date)

rep.data <- data[data$season=="Spring",]

#citation('GGally')

Reduce Climate covariates to tmean, tdmean and ppt

Linear Models Comparison

Information Theoretic Approach

Create 10 Models with less than 10 covariates each with a hypothesis as to why that would be a an appropriate model

I am not going to predict so I am going to use the full dataset for these models to be able to infer what are the most important variables

I am going to use a different color for each variable, I’ll list them here

Intercept = Black Zi Intercept = Dark Grey ppt = Blue lag.ppt = dodgerblue2 zi ppt = blueviolet zi lag.ppt = blue4 fire = red tmean =

Abundance

data <- na.omit(data)
#hist(data$abundance)

set.seed(4)
###

#Options for random effects: (1|Block) or (1|Block/yst)
# I'm going with (1|Block) because (1|Block/yst) is overfitting according diagnose(lag.abun)
#Remove the random effect from the zero inflation

abun.null <- glmmTMB(data = data, abundance ~ 1 + (1|BLOCK), 
                     zi=~ 1 + (1|BLOCK),
                     family = "poisson") # Null Model

abun.global <- glmmTMB(data = data, abundance ~ ppt + lag.ppt + tmean + lag.tmean + Fire + (1|BLOCK),
                     zi=~ ppt + lag.ppt + tmean + lag.tmean  + Fire + (1|BLOCK),
                     family = "poisson") # Hyp: All factors contribute to rodent abundance)

abun.fire <- glmmTMB(data = data, abundance ~ Fire + (1|BLOCK), 
                     zi=~ Fire+ (1|BLOCK),
                     family = "poisson") # Hyp: Fire is the main driver of rodent abundance through vegetation removal

abun.current <- glmmTMB(data = data, abundance ~ ppt + tmean  + (1|BLOCK),
                        zi=~ ppt + tmean+ (1|BLOCK),
                      family = "poisson")                                             # Hyp: Current weather conditions drive rodent abundance

abun.lag <- glmmTMB(data = data, abundance ~ lag.ppt + lag.tmean +  (1|BLOCK),
                    zi=~lag.ppt + lag.tmean + (1|BLOCK),
                      family = "poisson")                                             # Hyp: Previous years weather drives rodent abundance

abun.ppt <- glmmTMB(data = data, abundance ~ lag.ppt + ppt  + (1|BLOCK),
                    zi=~ lag.ppt + ppt  + (1|BLOCK),
                      family = "poisson")                                             # Hyp: Precipitation drives rodent abundance

abun.temp <- glmmTMB(data = data, abundance ~ tmean + lag.tmean +  (1|BLOCK),
                     zi=~ tmean + lag.tmean+ (1|BLOCK),
                     family = "poisson")                               # Hyp: Temperature drives rodent abundance

abun.fire.ppt <- glmmTMB(data = data, abundance ~ ppt * Fire + lag.ppt * Fire + (1|BLOCK),
                         zi=~  ppt * Fire + lag.ppt * Fire + (1|BLOCK),
                         family = "poisson")                               # Hyp: Interaction between fire and precipitation drives rodent abundance

abun.fire.temp <- glmmTMB(data = data, abundance ~ Fire * tmean + Fire * lag.tmean  +(1|BLOCK),
                          zi=~ Fire * tmean + Fire * lag.tmean+ (1|BLOCK),
                        family = "poisson")                                         # Hyp: The interaction between fire and temperature drives rodent abundance


abun.sel <- model.sel(abun.null, abun.global, abun.fire, abun.current, abun.lag, abun.ppt, abun.temp, abun.fire.ppt, abun.fire.temp)

moj.abun.coefs <- c

# Calculate 95% confidence intervals manually
moj.abun.coefs <- data.frame(
  term = rownames(c),
  estimate = c[, "Estimate"],
  conf.low = c[, "Estimate"] - 1.96 * c[, "Std..Error"],
  conf.high = c[, "Estimate"] + 1.96 * c[, "Std..Error"]
)

# Filter coefficients where confidence intervals do not cross 0
moj.abun.coefs_filtered <- moj.abun.coefs[moj.abun.coefs$conf.low > 0 | moj.abun.coefs$conf.high < 0, ]

                     family = "compois") # Hyp: Fire is the main driver of rodent richness through vegetation removal

                 zi=~ tmean + lag.tmean ,

  term = rownames(moj.si.coefs),
  estimate = moj.si.coefs[, "Estimate"],
  conf.low = moj.si.coefs[, "Estimate"] - 1.96 * moj.si.coefs[, "Std..Error"],
  conf.high = moj.si.coefs[, "Estimate"] + 1.96 * moj.si.coefs[, "Std..Error"]
)

  "lag.ppt1" = "Zi lag.ppt",
  "cond(lag.ppt)" = "lag.ppt"
)

moj.si.coefs$term <-new_labels[moj.si.coefs$term]

# Filter coefficients where confidence intervals do not cross 0
moj.si.coefs_filtered <- moj.si.coefs[moj.si.coefs$conf.low > 0 | moj.si.coefs$conf.high < 0, ]

moj.sh.coefs_filtered <- moj.sh.coefs[moj.sh.coefs$conf.low > 0 | moj.sh.coefs$conf.high < 0, ]
moj.sh.coefs_filtered
##          term   estimate   conf.low  conf.high

new_labels = c(
  "(Intercept)" = "Intercept",
  "lag.ppt1" = "Zi lag.ppt"
)

moj.sh.coefs_filtered$term <- new_labels[moj.sh.coefs_filtered$term]

# Create the coefficient plot
moj.sh.coplot <- ggplot(moj.sh.coefs_filtered, aes(x = term, y = estimate, color = term)) +
  geom_point(size = 3) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = conf.low, ymax = conf.high), width = 0.2) +
    geom_hline(yintercept = 0, color = "grey", linetype = "dashed") +  # Add grey dashed line at y = 0
  labs(x = "Mojave Shannon's Diversity", y = "Coefficient Estimate") +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("black", "blue4"))+

  coord_flip() +# Optional: Flip coordinates for horizontal bars
  theme(plot.title    = element_text(size=12,   colour = "black", family = "serif"),

brru <- read.csv("BRRU_density.csv")

brru <- brru |> mutate(Fire= substr(Plot,1,1))
brru <- brru |> mutate(rodents= substr(Plot,2,2))
brru <- brru |> filter(rodents == "S")

brru <- brru |> select(Block, Fire, Year, BRRU.density, TAP, MAT)

colnames(brru) <- c("BLOCK", "Fire", "Year", "BRRU", "TAP", "MAT")

moj.semdata <- merge(rep.data, brru, by = c("Year", "Fire", "BLOCK"))
moj.semdata$BRRU <- scale(moj.semdata$BRRU)
moj.semdata$TAP <- scale(moj.semdata$TAP)
moj.semdata$MAT <- scale(moj.semdata$MAT)

Add R squareds to the lavaan model outputs

# Abundance

# Extract R-squared values
rsquared <- inspect(sem.abun.fit, "r2")

# Customize node labels to include R-squared
custom_labels <- list(
  BRRU = paste0("BRRU\nR² = ", round(rsquared["BRRU"], 2)),
  abundance = paste0("abundance\nR² = ", round(rsquared["abundance"], 2))
)

# Generate the plot with custom labels
moj.abun.sem.plot <- lavaanPlot(
  name = "semabun",
  sem.abun.fit,
  coefs = TRUE,
  stand = TRUE,        # Include standardized coefficients if needed
  node_options = list(shape = "box", fontname = "Helvetica"),
  edge_options = list(color = "black"),
  labels = custom_labels
)

# Print the plot
moj.abun.sem.plot
